ZH: 疫苗是预防疾病的有效方式之一。
EN: Vaccines are one of the effective ways to prevent diseases.

ZH: 这个疫苗可以保护你免受流感病毒的侵袭。
EN: This vaccine can protect you from the attack of the influenza virus.

ZH: 医生建议每年接种一次流感疫苗。
EN: Doctors recommend getting a flu vaccine once a year.

ZH: 孩子们需要打疫苗来保护免受传染病的侵害。
EN: Children need to get vaccinated to protect them from infectious diseases.

ZH: 疫苗接种是一项必要的健康保护措施。
EN: Vaccination is a necessary healthcare measure.

ZH: 这种疫苗需要多次接种来产生充分的免疫力。
EN: This vaccine requires multiple doses to establish full immunity.

ZH: 各个国家正在努力开发新冠疫苗。
EN: Countries around the world are working hard to develop a COVID-19 vaccine.

ZH: 接种疫苗是为了保障个人和社会的健康安全。
EN: Vaccination is for the health and safety of individuals and society.

ZH: 我们需要积极宣传疫苗的重要性。
EN: We need to actively promote the importance of vaccines.

ZH: 接种疫苗是责任与义务。
EN: Getting vaccinated is a responsibility and obligation.

ZH: 在接种疫苗后，一些轻微的副作用是正常的。
EN: Some mild side effects are normal after receiving a vaccine.

ZH: 疫苗接种对于消灭一些疾病非常重要。
EN: Vaccination is crucial for the eradication of certain diseases.

ZH: 疫苗的研发需要经过严格的临床试验。
EN: Vaccine development requires rigorous clinical trials.

ZH: 这种疫苗已经被证明能够有效预防疾病。
EN: This vaccine has been proven to be effective in preventing diseases.

ZH: 疫苗接种计划是由政府制定的。
EN: Vaccination schedules are established by the government.

ZH: 接种疫苗可以帮助身体建立免疫屏障。
EN: Vaccination can help the body establish an immune barrier.

ZH: 我们应该相信科学，在医生的指导下接种疫苗。
EN: We should trust in science and get vaccinated under the guidance of doctors.

ZH: 疫苗的研制需要投入大量的资源和时间。
EN: Developing vaccines requires a significant investment of resources and time.

ZH: 疫苗是医学进步的重要成果之一。
EN: Vaccines are one of the important achievements of medical progress.
